# Runtime artifacts and temp files
tmp/
*.tmp

# Local debug logs and stray files that have accumulated in the repo root.
# actions.jsonl is written by some tooling; run_type was a one-off scratch
# file; supabase/snippets/ is Supabase Studio's local snippet cache.
actions.jsonl
services/api/actions.jsonl
run_type
supabase/snippets/

# Staging and environment variants
.env.staging
.env.production
.env.*.local
# Exception: the scanner's .env.production contains ONLY public values
# (Supabase URL + anon key + store_id — all designed to be safe in client
# bundles). It must be committed so the Docker build can bake them in.
# Service-role keys and other secrets NEVER go here — they live in fly secrets.
!apps/scanner/.env.production
supabase/.temp/
supabase/.branches/
tmp/data/

# Locally-trusted dev TLS certs (mkcert) — never commit private keys
*.pem
*-key.pem

# Vite/Vitest config loader writes a transient compiled copy of
# vitest.config.ts next to itself on each run (e.g.
# vitest.config.ts.timestamp-*.mjs). Never commit these.
*.timestamp-*.mjs

# Family-grouping audit reports (generated by scripts/audit-family-grouping.mjs;
# derived from prod data — regenerate, never commit)
family-audit/

# Obsidian vault config (2026-07-23): Tony's vault points AT this repo so
# docs/lk reads as a linked knowledge base. Editor state/workspace files are
# machine-local noise — never commit. The docs themselves stay canonical and
# versioned; Obsidian is a VIEW, never a second store (RULEBOOK #27).
.obsidian/
